ue_id":"019b81f3-1f39-793d-8cf9-3fc5f55ec767","event_date":"2017-07-19","event_kind":"race","event_name":"Wednesday Evening Series #3 - Big Finn Hill","venue_name":"Big Finn Hill Park","event_notes":null,"course_count":4,"event_status":null,"result_count":66,"citation_count":3,"event_comments":"The third event in this year’s Wednesday Evening Series! The Wednesday Evening Series is our most relaxed, casual set of navigation events, held in local parks once the weather warms up. These events are a little more low-key than those in the WIOL/Winter Series, and we always offer a barbeque afterward for all participants. Decompress after work, with or without your coworkers. Or meet your family at the park and enjoy a night off from cooking. Or meet a bunch of friends at the park for an evening of exploring together, chatting over some food, and finishing up with frisbee on the lawn.\nEvents in the Wednesday Evening Series are generally less challenging (both physically and navigationally) than many of our other events, and are therefore great for beginners and those less experienced with orienteering – while also offering a challenge to longtime participants of the sport.\nCheck back later for special notes from the Course Designer(s). Big Finn Hill Park is relatively large and rugged (as compared to most of our WES venues) and thickly forested for the most part. The park is very popular with mountain bikers, and as such certain sections of the park offer some of the most windy, complicated trail networks you’ll find on any of our maps – which makes for fun orienteering! You can expect a course at Big Finn Hill to take longer to complete than a course of similar length at other events in the Wednesday Evening Series. Also, the park is bisected by Juanita Drive NE, a high-speed arterial, and the more advanced courses will cross the road twice – please be careful when crossing!","external_links":[{"link_url":"https://goo.gl/maps/np1khUBRX5t","link_type":"directions"},{"link_url":"https://cascadeoc.org/event/wednesday-evening-3-2/","link_type":"event_page"},{"link_url":"https://cascadeoc.org/map/big-finn-hill/","link_type":"map"},{"link_url":"http://rg.cascadeoc.org/rg2/#183","link_type":"routegadget"},{"link_url":"https://cascadeoc.org/series/wednesday-evening/","link_type":"series"},{"link_url":"http://obasen.orientering.se/winsplits/online/en/default.asp?page=classes&databaseId=50226","link_type":"splits"}],"volunteer_roles":[{"role_name":"Course Designer","individual_id":"019b7ac9-920b-7530-b85a-103e52302ff8","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Will Enger","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null},{"role_name":"Epunch Coordinator","individual_id":"01913919-da03-757e-b829-aa2bdc684400","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Debbie Newell","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null}],"organizing_club_id":"01912f3e-e3e1-7e8e-b3c6-32387a8b4990","result_source_brief":"CascadeOC Website: https://www.cascadeoc.org/result/wednesday-evening-series-3-big-finn-hill-2/","organizing_club_name":"Cascade Orienteering Club","cumulative_event_comments":"The third event in this year’s Wednesday Evening Series! The Wednesday Evening Series is our most relaxed, casual set of navigation events, held in local parks once the weather warms up. These events are a little more low-key than those in the WIOL/Winter Series, and we always offer a barbeque afterward for all participants. Decompress after work, with or without your coworkers. Or meet your family at the park and enjoy a night off from cooking. Or meet a bunch of friends at the park for an evening of exploring together, chatting over some food, and finishing up with frisbee on the lawn.\nEvents in the Wednesday Evening Series are generally less challenging (both physically and navigationally) than many of our other events, and are therefore great for beginners and those less experienced with orienteering – while also offering a challenge to longtime participants of the sport.\nCheck back later for special notes from the Course Designer(s). Big Finn Hill Park is relatively large and rugged (as compared to most of our WES venues) and thickly forested for the most part. The park is very popular with mountain bikers, and as such certain sections of the park offer some of the most windy, complicated trail networks you’ll find on any of our maps – which makes for fun orienteering! You can expect a course at Big Finn Hill to take longer to complete than a course of similar length at other events in the Wednesday Evening Series. Also, the park is bisected by Juanita Drive NE, a high-speed arterial, and the more advanced courses will cross the road twice – please be careful when crossing!"}
